ense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"blame_sng_4\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"labels\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"labels\">(informal)</span></span> <span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">used to say that you think that what somebody did was reasonable and the right thing to do</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">‘I just slammed the phone down when he said that.’ ‘I don't blame you!’</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span> <span class=\"idm-g\" id=\"blame_idmg_4\" sk=\"onlyhaveyourselftoblame\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"blame_topg_6\"><div class=\"webtop\"><span class=\"idm\" id=\"blame_idm_4\">only have yourself to blame <span class=\"idmsep\">|</span> have nobody/no one to blame but yourself</span> </div></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"blame_sng_5\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">used to say that you think something is somebody’s own fault</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">If you lose your job, you'll only have yourself to blame.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span></div><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/blame_1\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">blame</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/blame1\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">blame</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href